### PHP Error Handling

Error handling is the process of catching and responding to errors in your PHP code.

### Error Types in PHP

| Type | Constant | Description |
|------|----------|-------------|
| 1 | `E_ERROR` | Fatal runtime error (script stops) |
| 2 | `E_WARNING` | Non-fatal warning |
| 4 | `E_PARSE` | Syntax error |
| 8 | `E_NOTICE` | Runtime notice (minor) |
| 256 | `E_USER_ERROR` | User-generated error |
| 512 | `E_USER_WARNING` | User-generated warning |
| 2048 | `E_STRICT` | PHP suggests code changes |
| 8191 | `E_ALL` | All errors and warnings |

### Custom Error Handler

```php
<?php
function customError($errno, $errstr, $errfile, $errline) {
    echo "<b>Error:</b> [$errno] $errstr<br>";
    echo "File: $errfile (Line: $errline)<br>";
}

set_error_handler("customError");

// Trigger error
echo 10 / 0; // Division by zero warning
?>
```

### Error Control Operator

```php
<?php
// Suppress errors with @
$value = @file_get_contents("nonexistent.txt");
if ($value === false) {
    echo "File not found (error suppressed)";
}
?>
```

### Error Reporting Settings

```php
<?php
// Report all errors except notices
error_reporting(E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE);

// Display errors (development)
ini_set("display_errors", 1);

// Log errors (production)
ini_set("log_errors", 1);
ini_set("error_log", "/path/to/error.log");
?>
```

> **Key Point:** In production, disable `display_errors` and enable `log_errors` to prevent sensitive information from being shown to users.
